reviewText: So-so documentary on Australian wildlife. It tries to cram in too much in 53 minutes, with poor background music and a badly written script. For example, a wombat is said to dig a burrow "longer than a very long truck." Why not just give the length in meters or feet? What is a "very long truck"?  Many species are shown fleetingly, but there is good footage of black swans, the lyre bird and dingoes.
Bought for grandkids and they love it
I lived in Australia for a few years and never knew the things show on this DVD.  Wish I had bought it before I moved back to the US so that I could visit the islands.
I bought this DVD for my son.  He loves it...all the Grainger collectios are full of good facts.
